Each page now has its own class which overrides type of UIViewPage. - Background colour of the page can be set by overriding UIViewPage.backgroundColor() - A piece of code can run when the page is loaded
column5: this can be done by overriding UIViewPage.viewDidLoad() - The page can be setup (elements added) by overriding an abstract method UIViewPage.setUp() - The page number has to be set by overriding an abstract method UIViewPage.pageNumber() - To switch to another page
column6: use UIViewPage.push(). If calling from inside a button method use MyClass.this.push(new anotherPage())
